Blue texts (comments) as should be ommitted from laser cutting (hide before file export).
Red lines should all be of 0.1mm line stroke and are laser cuts.
Green lines are similar but just engrave the surface for marks.
Black is for bitmap/area engraving with 200 dpi or so.
All slits are dimensioned for a material thickness of 3-3.2 mm.
We used "HDF" and our plates were 600 x 425 mm. If you use color coated HDF, laser with colored side facing up.
The precut kit and the prism glasses for over/under (right/left view) stereo viewing can be
